as the example you gave Christians,

17:41.000 --> 17:43.000
or new age,

17:43.000 --> 17:45.000
whatever, religion, really,

17:45.000 --> 17:47.000
including Buddhism,

17:47.000 --> 17:49.000
when they start over.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.000
It's the ultimate consciousness.

17:51.000 --> 17:53.000
It's the pure consciousness.

17:53.000 --> 17:55.000
That consciousness is this consciousness.

17:55.000 --> 17:57.000
You overmystify that presence,

17:57.000 --> 17:59.000
but if there is nothing present,

17:59.000 --> 18:01.000
you can't have the presence.

18:01.000 --> 18:03.000
You need to have a thing

18:03.000 --> 18:05.000
in order for it to appear.

18:05.000 --> 18:07.000
So, that's why consciousness is

18:07.000 --> 18:09.000
not independent.

18:09.000 --> 18:11.000
It requires Nama Rupa.

18:11.000 --> 18:13.000
If there isn't,

18:13.000 --> 18:15.000
consciousness could not

18:15.000 --> 18:17.000
be discerned.

18:17.000 --> 18:19.000
So, as much as

18:19.000 --> 18:21.000
consciousness determines that

18:21.000 --> 18:23.000
which appears,

18:23.000 --> 18:25.000
allows it to appear

18:25.000 --> 18:27.000
to the same extent that which has appeared,

18:27.000 --> 18:29.000
defines consciousness.

18:29.000 --> 18:31.000
Otherwise, it wouldn't be there.

18:31.000 --> 18:33.000
Consciousness is just

18:33.000 --> 18:35.000
a six kind.

18:35.000 --> 18:37.000
In particular,

18:37.000 --> 18:39.000
you don't have to think of them

18:39.000 --> 18:41.000
at the same time,

18:41.000 --> 18:43.000
because they get complicated,

18:43.000 --> 18:45.000
but you can take a sense.

18:45.000 --> 18:47.000
Eyes are conscious.

18:47.000 --> 18:49.000
Eyes are conscious.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.000
That's the thing.

18:51.000 --> 18:53.000
Most of people automatically assume

18:53.000 --> 18:55.000
matter is out there,

18:55.000 --> 18:57.000
consciousness is in here.

18:57.000 --> 18:59.000
But actually matter

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
and consciousness

19:01.000 --> 19:03.000
are on the same level

19:03.000 --> 19:05.000
out there.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.000
And their relationship

19:07.000 --> 19:09.000
is known as Nama Rupa.

19:09.000 --> 19:11.000
And that can have the internal aspect

19:11.000 --> 19:13.000
and external aspect.

19:13.000 --> 19:15.000
So actually, consciousness

19:15.000 --> 19:17.000
is out there with the things.

19:17.000 --> 19:19.000
Which is why

19:19.000 --> 19:21.000
it can never be yourself.

19:21.000 --> 19:23.000
For as long as you think

19:23.000 --> 19:25.000
it's in here,

19:25.000 --> 19:27.000
you will be taking it as me.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.000
But if you see it out there,

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
in that material world,

19:31.000 --> 19:33.000
then you realize,

19:33.000 --> 19:35.000
well, I cannot have that

19:35.000 --> 19:37.000
nothing more than I could

19:37.000 --> 19:39.000
have matter to be mine.

19:39.000 --> 19:41.000
And that's

19:41.000 --> 19:43.000
what Yonero is talking about

19:43.000 --> 19:45.000
instead of different terms.

19:45.000 --> 19:47.000
When he was saying that Rupa

19:47.000 --> 19:49.000
and Vinyana,

19:49.000 --> 19:51.000
they were

19:51.000 --> 19:53.000
well superimposed

19:53.000 --> 19:55.000
or just like two different things

19:55.000 --> 19:57.000
but they come together.

19:57.000 --> 19:59.000
They don't mix.

19:59.000 --> 20:01.000
I mean, they just get associated.

20:01.000 --> 20:03.000
The result of that

20:03.000 --> 20:05.000
is Nama Rupa.

20:05.000 --> 20:07.000
It's the whole world

20:07.000 --> 20:09.000
that you know that you can never know

20:09.000 --> 20:11.000
your past, your future.

20:11.000 --> 20:13.000
It's all within Nama Rupa.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.000
Within the conscious matter.

20:15.000 --> 20:17.000
Because if your consciousness is truly

20:17.000 --> 20:21.000
in you, it would be independent from the body.

20:21.000 --> 20:23.000
But when that material body

20:23.000 --> 20:25.000
gets disintegrated,

20:25.000 --> 20:27.000
consciousness goes.

20:27.000 --> 20:29.000
It cannot stay.

20:29.000 --> 20:31.000
You mean that the sense of self.

20:31.000 --> 20:33.000
Sense of self.

20:33.000 --> 20:35.000
The consciousness is in the body,

20:35.000 --> 20:37.000
you know?

20:37.000 --> 20:39.000
No.

20:39.000 --> 20:41.000
Why would it be?

20:41.000 --> 20:43.000
With the consciousness,

20:43.000 --> 20:45.000
this body consciousness is associated

20:45.000 --> 20:46.000
with the body.

20:46.000 --> 20:48.000
The reason you can look in or out

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
or in and out or wherever you want

20:50.000 --> 20:54.000
is because you are already conscious.

20:54.000 --> 20:56.000
So the sense of space

20:56.000 --> 20:58.000
the direction where you look

20:58.000 --> 21:00.000
is possible only because

21:00.000 --> 21:02.000
the body is already conscious.

21:02.000 --> 21:04.000
The consciousness, the five aggregates

21:04.000 --> 21:06.000
are already there.

21:06.000 --> 21:08.000
So it's secondary to that.

21:08.000 --> 21:10.000
If it's secondary means

21:10.000 --> 21:12.000
you can't use it then to find

21:12.000 --> 21:14.000
its origin.

21:14.000 --> 21:16.000
Not the origin.

21:16.000 --> 21:18.000
And if you, you know,

21:18.000 --> 21:20.000
you look in the distance and you see

21:20.000 --> 21:22.000
the tree really, really far out.

21:22.000 --> 21:26.000
Well, your consciousness is out there.

21:26.000 --> 21:28.000
Consciousness is out there.

21:28.000 --> 21:30.000
I mean the...

21:30.000 --> 21:32.000
Doesn't mean it's in that matter.

21:32.000 --> 21:34.000
Means it's associated with that matter.

21:34.000 --> 21:36.000
No matter how far it is.

21:36.000 --> 21:38.000
Whether it's in your thoughts or through your senses.

21:38.000 --> 21:42.000
It's actually external.

21:42.000 --> 21:44.000
For other hand,

21:44.000 --> 21:46.000
all of the aggregates become external.

21:46.000 --> 21:48.000
Externally.

21:48.000 --> 21:50.000
External means you mean

21:50.000 --> 21:52.000
that they're not serve in the...

21:52.000 --> 21:54.000
Well, yes, for other hand, yes.

21:54.000 --> 21:56.000
External means not serve.

21:56.000 --> 21:58.000
And the Buddha did say that

21:58.000 --> 22:02.000
for somebody completely free from ignorance,

22:02.000 --> 22:04.000
what is left is

22:04.000 --> 22:06.000
this conscious body

22:06.000 --> 22:08.000
and all

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
whatever name and form externally.

22:10.000 --> 22:12.000
That's what's left.

22:12.000 --> 22:14.000
So the body

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
that is associated with the consciousness

22:16.000 --> 22:18.000
or consciousness associated with the body

22:18.000 --> 22:20.000
is just like

22:20.000 --> 22:22.000
two completely different things

22:22.000 --> 22:24.000
that kind of come and stop together

22:24.000 --> 22:26.000
which is the birth.

22:26.000 --> 22:28.000
But then

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
when one of them goes

22:30.000 --> 22:32.000
the other one cannot remain standing.

22:32.000 --> 22:34.000
But it's not that consciousness enters

22:34.000 --> 22:36.000
in the body.

22:36.000 --> 22:38.000
Because any notion of space

22:38.000 --> 22:40.000
is the fact that you're conscious.

22:40.000 --> 22:42.000
So consciousness cannot be

22:42.000 --> 22:44.000
in its own result.

22:44.000 --> 22:46.000
For other hand,

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
does any idea appear that

22:48.000 --> 22:50.000
as my body, but the thought itself

22:50.000 --> 22:52.000
is not this.

22:52.000 --> 22:54.000
Well, even when he thinks my

22:54.000 --> 22:56.000
eye, I am or I am this

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
or this is my carp order,

22:58.000 --> 23:00.000
that doesn't imply

23:00.000 --> 23:02.000
the emotional significance

23:02.000 --> 23:04.000
of me and sense of self.

23:04.000 --> 23:06.000
In other words, I can say that's my cup

23:06.000 --> 23:08.000
but if somebody comes and steal it

23:08.000 --> 23:10.000
I won't suffer an account of it.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.000
But as a designation of speech

23:12.000 --> 23:14.000
you can, you know, in the Buddha said that.

23:14.000 --> 23:16.000
Well, the target that says I am

23:16.000 --> 23:18.000
but it doesn't mean that he really thinks he is.

23:18.000 --> 23:20.000
He's just the figure of speech

23:20.000 --> 23:22.000
becomes for him.

23:22.000 --> 23:24.000
Where a practitioner, when he says

23:24.000 --> 23:26.000
I am for him, that is his sense of self.

23:26.000 --> 23:30.000
So as a designation, it's valid.

23:30.000 --> 23:32.000
You have to designate it somehow.

23:32.000 --> 23:34.000
He's just a misunderstanding

23:34.000 --> 23:35.000
that goes with it.

23:35.000 --> 23:37.000
That's removed.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.000
In case of an other hand.

23:39.000 --> 23:41.000
You thought itself was different?

23:41.000 --> 23:43.000
Actually, different, you know, I think?

23:43.000 --> 23:45.000
Well, differently as much as there is no

23:45.000 --> 23:47.000
greedy version of the illusion ever.

23:47.000 --> 23:49.000
Again, to arise.

23:49.000 --> 23:51.000
Well, they cannot appear.

23:51.000 --> 23:53.000
Cannot.

23:53.000 --> 23:55.000
No. So, he's not just temporarily free from

23:55.000 --> 23:57.000
greedy version of the illusion.

23:57.000 --> 23:59.000
An other hand, he's free from

23:59.000 --> 24:01.000
a possibility of those things arising.

24:01.000 --> 24:03.000
Which is why he's another hand.

24:03.000 --> 24:05.000
There might be pleasing thoughts,

24:05.000 --> 24:07.000
displeasing thoughts, neutral thoughts.

24:07.000 --> 24:09.000
